original_title: Brooklyn: Old Mill Road - Newton Avenue
text:
(1) Old Mill Road, also known as "Plunders Neck Road", showing a home razed subsequent to 1917. This house according to the photographer is one half mile south of New Lots Road, which would place this house in one of these three locations, either the N.W. or N.E. corners of Fairfield Aves., and Crescent Street, or the N.W. corner of Wortman Ave., and Hemlock Street.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, another view.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, another angle.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
